@startuml Sequence Diagram - Photo Viewer Interaction
!theme cerulean-outline

title SmartMedia - Photo Viewer & Editing Sequence

actor User
participant "HomePage" as Home
participant "PhotoViewer\nComponent" as Viewer
participant "AppStore" as Store
participant "Electron\nIPC" as IPC
participant "File System" as FS

User -> Home: Click image in gallery
activate Home

Home -> Home: Get image metadata\nand index

Home -> Viewer: Open PhotoViewer\n(image, index)
activate Viewer

Viewer -> Viewer: Load image preview\nfrom cache

Viewer -> User: Display full-screen\nimage with overlay
deactivate Home

== Basic Viewing ==

User -> Viewer: Press arrow keys /\nclick navigation
activate User

Viewer -> Viewer: Calculate next/previous\nindex

Viewer -> Store: Get adjacent image
activate Store
Store -> Viewer: ImageMetadata
deactivate Store

Viewer -> Viewer: Update displayed image

Viewer -> User: Show new image\nwith animation

deactivate User

== Metadata Panel ==

User -> Viewer: Click "Info" icon
activate User

Viewer -> Viewer: Toggle metadata panel

Viewer -> User: Show panel with:\n• Caption\n• Tags\n• Objects\n• Face count\n• Scene\n• Date

User -> Viewer: Click tag chip
Viewer -> Store: Add tag to search
activate Store
Store -> Store: Update searchQuery\nand filters
deactivate Store

Viewer -> Viewer: Close viewer

Viewer -> Home: Return to gallery\nwith applied filters

deactivate User

== Editing Mode ==

User -> Viewer: Click "Edit" button
activate User

Viewer -> Viewer: setIsEditing(true)

Viewer -> User: Show editing controls:\n• Brightness\n• Contrast\n• Saturation\n• Sharpness\n• Blur\n• Rotate\n• Flip

User -> Viewer: Adjust brightness slider

Viewer -> Viewer: Update editState

Viewer -> Viewer: Apply CSS filters\nin real-time

Viewer -> User: Show live preview

User -> Viewer: Adjust multiple settings

Viewer -> Viewer: Track all changes\nin editState

User -> Viewer: Click "Save"

Viewer -> Viewer: Check if edits were made

alt User wants to save as copy
  
  User -> Viewer: Click "Save as Copy"
  
  Viewer -> Store: saveImageAsCopy(\nid, editState)
  activate Store
  
  Store -> Store: Create new ImageMetadata\nwith edited values
  
  Store -> Store: Generate new ID\nand filename
  
  Store -> IPC: saveImage(newMetadata)
  activate IPC
  
  IPC -> FS: Write to database
  activate FS
  
  FS -> IPC: Success
  deactivate FS
  
  IPC -> Store: Image saved
  deactivate IPC
  
  Store -> Store: Add to images array
  
  Store -> Viewer: New image created
  deactivate Store
  
  Viewer -> User: Show "Saved as copy"\nmessage
  
else User wants to overwrite original
  
  User -> Viewer: Click "Save Original"
  
  Viewer -> Viewer: Show confirmation dialog
  
  User -> Viewer: Confirm
  
  Viewer -> Store: saveImageAsOriginal(\nid, editState)
  activate Store
  
  Store -> Store: Update existing\nImageMetadata
  
  Store -> IPC: updateImage(id, edits)
  activate IPC
  
  IPC -> FS: UPDATE database
  activate FS
  
  FS -> IPC: Success
  deactivate FS
  
  IPC -> Store: Updated
  deactivate IPC
  
  Store -> Viewer: Image updated
  deactivate Store
  
  Viewer -> User: Show "Original\noverwritten" message
  
end

Viewer -> Viewer: Reset editState\nExit editing mode

deactivate User

== AI Chat Integration ==

User -> Viewer: Click "AI Tools"
activate User

Viewer -> Viewer: Show AI options:\n• Suggest tags\n• Improve caption\n• Ask question

User -> Viewer: Click "Ask Question"

Viewer -> Viewer: Show text input

User -> Viewer: Type: "What's the\nlocation?"

Viewer -> IPC: aiChat(imagePath,\n"What's the location?")
activate IPC

IPC -> IPC: Forward to Python engine

IPC -> Viewer: AI response:\n"This appears to be\na beach in Hawaii"
deactivate IPC

Viewer -> User: Display AI answer\nin chat bubble

deactivate User

== Tag Management ==

User -> Viewer: Click "+" to add tag
activate User

Viewer -> Viewer: Show tag input field

User -> Viewer: Type "vacation"

Viewer -> Store: updateImage(id,\n{tags: [...tags, "vacation"]})
activate Store

Store -> IPC: saveImageTags(id, tags)
activate IPC

IPC -> FS: UPDATE images\nSET tags = ?
activate FS

FS -> IPC: Success
deactivate FS

IPC -> Store: Updated
deactivate IPC

Store -> Viewer: Tags updated
deactivate Store

Viewer -> Viewer: Update tag chips

Viewer -> User: Show new tag

deactivate User

== Favorite Toggle ==

User -> Viewer: Click heart icon
activate User

Viewer -> Store: toggleFavorite(imageId)
activate Store

Store -> Store: Update isFavorite flag

Store -> IPC: updateImage(id,\n{is_favorite: true})
activate IPC

IPC -> FS: UPDATE database
activate FS

FS -> IPC: Success
deactivate FS

IPC -> Store: Updated
deactivate IPC

Store -> Viewer: Favorite toggled
deactivate Store

Viewer -> Viewer: Update heart icon\n(filled/unfilled)

Viewer -> User: Show visual feedback

deactivate User

== Delete Image ==

User -> Viewer: Click trash icon
activate User

Viewer -> Viewer: Show confirmation dialog

User -> Viewer: Confirm deletion

Viewer -> Store: moveToTrash(imageId)
activate Store

Store -> Store: Move from images[]\nto trashedImages[]

Store -> IPC: deleteImage(id)
activate IPC

IPC -> FS: UPDATE images\nSET is_deleted = 1
activate FS

FS -> IPC: Success
deactivate FS

IPC -> Store: Deleted
deactivate IPC

Store -> Home: Trigger re-render
deactivate Store

Viewer -> Viewer: Close viewer

Viewer -> Home: Return to gallery
deactivate Viewer

Home -> User: Updated gallery\n(image removed)

deactivate User

note over User, Viewer
  **Keyboard Shortcuts**
  • ← → : Navigate
  • ESC : Close viewer
  • E : Edit mode
  • F : Toggle favorite
  • I : Show info
  • DEL : Delete
end note

note over Viewer, Store
  **Non-Destructive Edits**
  • Original never modified
    (unless explicitly chosen)
  • Edit state stored separately
  • Can save as copy
  • Undo by closing without saving
end note

@enduml
